---
title: Beef Tenderloin & Garlic Herb Pan Sauce with Creamed Kale & Fingerling Potatoes
description: Beef tenderloin is ultra-special. True to its name, this cut is luxuriously tender—perfect for impressing your dinner companion (and yourself). Here, it’s seared to develop a deep brown crust and then drizzled with a rich garlic herb pan sauce. Like any great steak-centric meal, this dish doesn’t skimp on the sides. Roasted fingerling potatoes are the perfect accompaniment for scooping up any extra sauce, while creamy, garlicky kale adds a deliciously hearty bite.
